HEADWORD: Heliostat
<hw>He"li*o*stat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Helio-</ets> + Gr. <?/ placed, standing, fr. <?/ to place,
stand: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧liostate</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
consisting of a mirror moved by clockwork, by which a sunbeam is made
apparently stationary, by being steadily directed to one spot during the
whole of its diurnal period; also, a geodetic heliotrope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

